<item>
            <title>[LU-7079] OSP shouldn&apos;t discard requests due to imp_peer_committed_transno</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7079</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;imp_peer_committed_transno isn&apos;t always actual. this leads to confusing sequence when req&apos;s commit_cb() is called, but imp_peer_committed_transno claims the request hasn&apos;t been committed yet. in this case we shouldn&apos;t release request, instead we have to put it back on opd_syn_committed_there list and wait till imp_peer_committed_transno is updated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
